Clinban — Development Changelog

Most recent entries appear first.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-21  clinban push, extended new, default type, and SCHEMA.md

  clinban push <id> advances a ticket one step forward through the workflow
  (backlog→in-progress, in-progress→done, blocked→in-progress). Exits 0 with
  an informational message when the ticket is already at the final status.

  clinban new now accepts optional positional arguments as body text. The
  editor opens with the body pre-filled; the user only needs to supply a title.

  default_type in .clinban pre-fills the type field in the interactive template
  and makes --type optional for --no-interactive creation.

  clinban init creates a fourth artifact, SCHEMA.md, at the project root — a
  human/LLM-readable reference covering ticket format, field constraints, status
  transitions, and agent operation instructions. Partial-init output now lists
  both existing and missing artifacts.

  The interactive ticket template shows a comment listing valid type values
  directly below the type field.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-19  Project initialization command

  clinban init creates the ticket directory, archive directory, and .clinban
  config file in one step. Supports --force for repairing partial setups.
  Default ticket layout moved from project root to tickets/ subdirectory.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-19  Editor integration and interactive ticket creation

  clinban new opens $EDITOR with a pre-populated template. After the editor
  closes, the ticket is linted and the user can reopen to fix errors.
  clinban edit follows the same loop — edits go through a temp copy and
  replace the live file only after parse and lint both pass.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-19  Data integrity hardening

  Six issues found in review: path containment check in register to prevent
  traversal, atomic write ordering, stricter ID uniqueness enforcement,
  consistent error wrapping, tightened lint rules, and FSM transition coverage.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-19  Full CLI surface

  All core commands landed: new --no-interactive, list (filtered, sorted),
  show, move (FSM-enforced transitions), archive (single and bulk with
  confirmation), register (adopt external files), lint (single or all),
  and shell completion via Cobra.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-18  Internal packages

  Foundation packages built independently and in dependency order:

  - ticket   — Ticket struct, Parse, Marshal, Status/Type constants
  - config   — .clinban TOML loading and path resolution
  - lint     — seven schema validation rules
  - fsm      — status transition table and ValidateTransition
  - slug     — ASCII-safe title-to-filename slugifier
  - editor   — $EDITOR process invocation with inherited stdio
  - store    — atomic writes, ID scanning, active/archive moves
  - template — embedded interactive ticket template

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2026-05-18  Project start

  Go module scaffolded. Planning pipeline (requirements, architecture, design,
  tasks) written before any implementation code.
